Parliament, Monday, 11 February 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Basic Education will tomorrow receive a briefing from the Department of Basic Education (DBE) and Umalusi on the 2018 National Senior Certificate Examination Outcomes. It will further receive a status report on schools reopening for the 2019 academic year and the state of school readiness in 2019. Details are as follows: 
	Date: Tuesday, 12 February 2019
	Time: 09:30
	Venue: Committee Room M314, Third Floor, Marks Building. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON BASIC EDUCATION, MS NOMALUNGELO GINA. For media enquiries or interviews, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Rajaa Azzakani (Ms)
	Tel: 021 403 8437
	Cell: 081 703 9542
	E-mail: razzakani@parliament.gov.za The room in which a House meets to debate is called a “Chamber”.Read more